 noon time the gentlemen are gathering in the downstair hall 
 talking about the war 
 mr borne enough insults from the meddling 
 yankees time we made them understand we keep our slaves with 
 or without their approval to stop them right from the state of 
 georgia to secede from the union man right 
 mr the south must assert ourselves by force of arms 
 after we fired on the yankee rascals at fort sumter got to fight 
 no other way man fight right fight man let the 
 be the ones to ask for peace mr the situation is 
 very simple the yankees fight and we can chorus 
 right mans what think just turn and run 
 
 every time 
 man one southerner can lick twenty yankees man 
 finish them in one battle gentlemen can always fight better than 
 rattle mans yes gentlemen always fight better than rattle mr 
 and what does the captain of our troop say ashley 
 well georgia fights i go with her but like my father i 
 hope that the yankees let us leave the union in peace man but 
 ashley man ashley insulted us mans you 
 mean that you want war ashley most of the miseries of the 
 world were caused by wars and when the wars were over no one 
 ever knew what they were about 
 mr now gentlemen mr butler has been up north i hear 
 you agree with us mr butler rhett butler i think 
 hard winning a war with words gentlemen 
 charles what do you mean sir rhett i mean mr hamilton 
 not a cannon factory in the whole south 
 man what difference does that make sir to a gentleman rhett 
 afraid going to make a great deal of difference to a great many 
 gentlemen sir charles are you hinting mr butler that the 
 yankees can lick us 
 rhett no not hinting saying very plainly that the yankees 
 are better equipped than we got 
 factories shipyards coalmines and a fleet to bottle up 
 our habours and starve us to death all got is cotton 
 and slaves and arrogance 
 man treacherous 
 charles i refuse to listen to any renegade talk 
 rhett well sorry if the truth offends you 
 charles apologies enough sir i hear you were 
 turned out of west point mr rhett butler and that you 
 received in an decent family in charleston not even 
 your own 
 rhett i apologize again for all my shortcomings mr 
 you mind if i walk about and look 
 over your place i seem to be spoiling brandy 
 and cigars of victory 
 rhett butler leaves the hall 
 man well just about what you could expect from 
 somebody like rhett butler 
 mr you did everything but call him out 
 charles he refused to fight 
 ashley not quite that charles he just refused to take 
 advantage of you 
 charles take advantage of me 
 ashley yes one of the best shots the country 
 proved a number of times against steadier hands and 
 cooler heads than yours 
 charles well show him 
 ashley no no no please go tweaking his nose 
 
 anymore you may be needed for more important fighting charles 
 now if excuse me mr our guest i think just show 
 him around ashley leaves the hall with intention of walking butler 
 around the house but before he can do this scarlett calls him into a 
 detached room scarlett ashley 
 ashley are you hiding from are you 
 up to why you upstairs resting with the other girls what is 
 this scarlett a secret scarlett well ashley ashley love 
 you ashley scarlett scarlett i love you i do 
 ashley well it enough that you gathered every other 
 heart today you always had mine you cut your teeth on it 
 scarlett oh tease me now have i your heart my darling 
 i love you i love you ashley you say such things 
 hate me for hearing them 
 scarlett oh i could never hate you and and i know you must 
 care about me oh you do care you ashley yes i care oh 
 we go away and forget we ever said these things 
 scarlett but how can we do that you you want to 
 marry me ashley going to marry melanie scarlett but 
 you not if you care for me 
 ashley oh my dear why must you make me say things that will 
 hurt you how can i make you understand so young and 
 thinking you know what marriage means 
 scarlett i know i love you and i want to be your wife you 
 love melanie 
 ashley like me scarlett part of my blood we 
 understand each other scarlett but you love me 
 ashley how could i help loving you you have all the passion for 
 life that i lack but that kind of love enough to make a successful 
 marriage for two people who are as different as we are 
 scarlett why you say it you coward afraid to 
 marry me rather live with that silly little fool who open 
 her mouth except to say yes raise a houseful of mealy 
 mouthed brats just like her ashley you say things like 
 that about melanie scarlett who are you to tell me i 
 you led me on you made me believe you wanted to marry me 
 ashley now scarlett be fair i never at any time scarlett 
 you did true you did hate you till i die i think of 
 anything bad enough to call you ashley leaves scarlett throws a 
 vase to the wall in anger the crashing of the vase startles rhett 
 butler he rises up from the couch in a dark corner of the room 
 rhett has the war started 
 scarlett sir should have made your presence known 
 rhett in the middle of that beautiful love scene that 
 have been very tactful would it but worry 
 your secret is safe with me 
 scarlett sir you are no gentleman 
 rhett and you miss are no lady think that i hold 
 that against you ladies have never held any charm for 
 me 
 scarlett first you take a low common advantage of 
 me then you insult me 
 rhett i meant it as a compliment and i hope to see 
 more of you when free of the spell of the elegant 
 mr wilkes he strike me as half good enough for 
 a girl of was passion for living 
 scarlett how dare you you fit to wipe his boot 
 rhett and you were going to hate him for the rest of 
 your life 
 
 
 
 
 
